,"target":"Author/Jaeuk Sim","line":120},{"title":"Author/Joo Yong Sim","target":"Author/Joo Yong Sim","line":121},{"title":"Author/Seong Min Hong","target":"Author/Seong Min Hong","line":122},{"title":"Author/Seong Min Hong","target":"Author/Seong Min Hong","line":123},{"title":"Author/Da Hye Yoon","target":"Author/Da Hye Yoon","line":124},{"title":"Author/Da Hye Yoon","target":"Author/Da Hye Yoon","line":125},{"title":"Author/Dae Hee Lee","target":"Author/Dae Hee Lee","line":126},{"title":"Author/Dong Hoon Lee","target":"Author/Dong Hoon Lee","line":127},{"title":"Author/Jae Kang Lee","target":"Author/Jae Kang Lee","line":128},{"title":"Author/Jae Kang Lee","target":"Author/Jae Kang Lee","line":129},{"title":"Author/Heesoon Lee","target":"Author/Heesoon Lee","line":130},{"title":"Author/Heesoon Lee","target":"Author/Heesoon Lee","line":131},{"title":"Author/Mi Kyeong Lee","target":"Author/Mi Kyeong Lee","line":132},{"title":"Author/Mi Kyeong Lee","target":"Author/Mi Kyeong Lee","line":133},{"title":"Author/Sun Yeou Kim","target":"Author/Sun Yeou Kim","line":134},{"title":"Author/Sun Yeou Kim","target":"Author/Sun Yeou Kim","line":135},{"title":"Author/Jae-Kyung Jung","target":"Author/Jae-Kyung Jung","line":136}],"metadata":{"id":"vishwanath_total_2022","type":"article-journal","title":"Total Synthesis of Isohericerinol A and Its Analogues to Access Their Potential Neurotrophic Effects","issued":{"date-parts":[[2022]]},"DOI":"10.1021/acs.joc.2c01096","container-title":"Journal of Organic Chemistry","abstract":"The secondary metabolites from Hericium erinaceus are well-known to have neurotrophic and neuroprotective effects. Isohericerinol A (1), isolated by our colleagues from its fruiting parts has a strong ability to increase the nerve growth factor secretion in C6 glioma cells. The current work describes the total synthesis of 1 and its regioisomer 5 in a few steps. We present two different approaches to 1 and a regiodivergent approach for both 1 and 5 by utilizing easily accessible feedstocks. Interestingly, the natural product 1, regioisomer 5, and their intermediates exhibited potent neurotrophic activity in in vitro experimental systems. Thus, these synthetic strategies provide access to a systematic structure-activity relationship study of natural product 1.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Vishwanath","given":"Manjunatha","literal":""},{"family":"Vishwanath","given":"Manjunatha","literal":""},{"family":"Chaudhary","given":"Chhabi Lal","literal":""},{"family":"Chaudhary","given":"Chhabi Lal","literal":""},{"family":"Park","given":"Yunjeong","literal":""},{"family":"Park","given":"Yunjeong","literal":""},{"family":"Viji","given":"Mayavan","literal":""},{"family":"Viji","given":"Mayavan","literal":""},{"family":"Jung","given":"Chanhyun","literal":""},{"family":"Cho","given":"Jungsook","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kwanghee","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kwanghee","literal":""},{"family":"Sim","given":"Jaeuk","literal":""},{"family":"Sim","given":"Joo Yong","literal":""},{"family":"Hong","given":"Seong Min","literal":""},{"family":"Hong","given":"Seong Min","literal":""},{"family":"Yoon","given":"Da Hye","literal":""},{"family":"Yoon","given":"Da Hye","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Dae Hee","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Dong Hoon","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Jae Kang","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Jae Kang","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Heesoon","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Heesoon","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Mi Kyeong","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Mi Kyeong","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Sun Yeou","literal":""},{"family":"Kim","given":"Sun Yeou","literal":""},{"family":"Jung","given":"Jae-Kyung","literal":""}],"citation-key":"vishwanath_total_2022","year":"2022","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Total Synthesis of Isohericerinol A and Its Analogues to Access Their Poten